cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper deals with learning the meaning of cardinals and quantifiers from visual scenes, which involves natural language processing, machine learning, and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes two models for learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the visual aspect of the problem could place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of neural mechanisms in humans could also make it relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
